23 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 14-301-306 is amended to read as follows:
24 14-301-306. Ownership of street or alley vesting in abutting owners —
25 Pending suits unaffected.
26 (a)(1) Upon the adoption of the ordinance, the absolute ownership of
27 the property abandoned by the city or town shall vest in the owners of the
28 real estate abutting thereon.
29 (2) Each such abutting owner shall take title to the center line
30 of the street or alley so abandoned, and the ownership shall be free from the
31 easement of the city or town for public use as a street or alley.
32 (b)(1) A future conveyance of real estate abutting a street or alley
33 abandoned by a city or town includes the respective portion of the street or
34 alley abandoned by the city or town that vested in the abutting owner upon
35 adoption of the ordinance unless an express reservation is made by the
36 abutting owner.
